		</div>
	{% endcapture %}

	{% render 'modal-button', text: "Standard Modal", modalId: "exampleModal1" %} <br><br>
	{% render 'modal', id: 'exampleModal1', heading: "Standard Modal", content: content_standard %}
	{% render 'modal', id: 'nestedModal1', heading: "Nested Modal", content: content_nested, class: "modal modal--standard modal--narrow modal--nested" %}

	{% comment %}
		Vimeo Modal
	{% endcomment %}

	{% capture content_vimeo %}
		<p class="modal__content rte">This modal has a type of 'vimeo'. It has the Vimeo video ID passed to the modal snippet, and that iFrame is then lazyloaded. This is set up so the snippet will work easily when using the <a href="https://shopify.dev/themes/architecture/settings/input-settings#video_url">section video_url input type</a>, which gives accesss to "id" and "type" for the video. Those values can be directly used with the modal snippet.</p>
	{% endcapture %}

	{% render 'modal-button', text: "Vimeo Modal", modalId: "exampleModal2" %} <br><br>
	{% render 'modal', id: 'exampleModal2', heading: "Vimeo Modal", type: 'vimeo', content: content_vimeo, video_id: '309872210' %}

	{% comment %}
		YouTube Modal
	{% endcomment %}

	{% capture content_youtube %}
		<p class="modal__content rte">This modal has a type of 'youtube'. It has the YouTube video ID passed to the modal snippet, and that iFrame is then lazyloaded. This is set up so the snippet will work easily when using the <a href="https://shopify.dev/themes/architecture/settings/input-settings#video_url">section video_url input type</a>, which gives accesss to "id" and "type" for the video. Those values can be directly used with the modal snippet.</p>
	{% endcapture %}

	{% render 'modal-button', text: "YouTube Modal", modalId: "exampleModal3" %}
	{% render 'modal', id: 'exampleModal3', heading: "YouTube Modal", type: 'youtube', content: content_youtube, video_id: 'slZd5cSAxOo' %}

</div>

